                        <p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                     <m> \text{Apply Trigonometry Using Sine}</m>
                                   </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Using the sine function to calculate the height of the object <m>AN</m>.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Drop a perpendicular line from Point A to meet line BC at N .
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        Formula:
                                        <md>
                                            <mrow> Height (AN) = \amp \text{Hypotenuse(AB)} \times \text{ sin }30^ \circ </mrow>
                                        </md>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        AN is therefore the height for triangle ABC.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        In a triangle <m>\text{sin} \theta = \frac{\text{Opposite}}{\text{Hypotenuse}}</m>. </p>
                                        <p>From the figure shown above, Opposite = AN, the height of triangle ABN whereas the hpotenuse i AB, the longest side of a tringle.
                                        
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Where <m>AN</m> = <m>\textbf{h}</m> and <m>BA</m> = <m>\textbf{a}</m>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                         <md>
                                           <mrow> \text{In triangle ABN, sin}30^ \circ = \amp \frac{AN}{AB} </mrow>
                                           <mrow> \text{sin } 30^ \circ  = \amp \frac{\textbf{a}}{\textbf{h}} </mrow> 
                                           <mrow> \text{ height of }\angle \text{ABC} = \amp \textbf{a} \text{sin } 30^ \circ  </mrow>
                                           <mrow> \text{ Since sin } 30^ \circ  = 1/2 a </mrow>
                                        </md>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        Area of Triangle ABC will be:
                                        <md>
                                            <mrow>\text{Triangle ABC} = \amp  \frac{1}{2}  \times \text {Base}\, \textbf{ (b)} \times  \text { Height}\, \textbf{(h)} =\textbf{a} \,\text{sin}\theta </mrow>
                                            <mrow> = \amp \frac{1}{2}\textbf{ ab }\textbf{ sin }\theta </mrow>
                                        </md>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    </ol>    

                </p>
            </statement>
