              <example>
    <statement>
      <p>
        If the length of the sides of a triangle <m>ABC</m> are <m>4</m> <em>m</em>, 
        <m>3</m> <em>m</em>, and <m>5</m> <em>m</em>. 
        Calculate its area using the heron's formula.
      </p>
      <image width="60%">
        <shortdescription>triangle</shortdescription>
        <latex-image>
          \begin{tikzpicture}
            % Define coordinates for the triangle
            \coordinate (A) at (0,0);
            \coordinate (B) at (4,0);
            \coordinate (C) at (1.8, 3); % Approximate the height of the triangle for this configuration

            % Draw the triangle
            \draw[thick] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- cycle;

            % Label the sides
            \node at (2, 0) [below] {4 m}; % side AB
            \node at (0.9, 1.5) [left] {5 m}; % side AC
            \node at (3.2, 1.5) [right] {3 m}; % side BC

            % Label the vertices
            \node at (A) [below left] {A};
            \node at (B) [below right] {B};
            \node at (C) [above] {C};
            
          \end{tikzpicture}
        </latex-image>
        
      </image>
    </statement>
    <solution>
      <p>
        To find: Area of the triangle <m>ABC</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Given that, <em>AB</em> <m>= 4</m> m, <em>BC</em> <m> = 3</m> m, <em>AC</em> <m>= 5</m>
      </p>
      <p>
        Using Heron's Formula,
        <md>
          <mrow>A \amp = \sqrt(s(s - a)(s - b)(s - c)) </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>s \amp = \frac{(a + b + c)}{2}</mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>s \amp = \frac{(4+3+5)}{2} </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> \amp = 6 \, \text{units} </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
      <p>
        Put the values,
        <md>
          <mrow>A \amp = \sqrt{(6(6 - 4)(6 - 3)(6 - 5))} </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>A \amp = \sqrt{(6 \text (2)\times(3)\times(1))} </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>A \amp = \sqrt{36} </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> \amp = 6 \, m^2</mrow>
        </md>
        The area of the triangle is <m>6 \, m^2</m>.
      </p>
    </solution>
